	- Missing B47&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp; - March 10, 1956&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp; - A B-47 carrying two nuclear weapon cores from MacDill Air Force Base in Florida to an overseas airbase disappeared during a scheduled air-to-air refueling over the Mediterranean Sea.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp; - After becoming lost in a thick cloud bank at 14,500 feet, the plane was never heard from again and its wreckage, including the nuclear cores, was never found. - Mark 15 thermonuclear bombs (commonly carried by B-47s) would have had a combined yield of 3.4 megatons.&lt;/p&gt;
